latestIgtvVideos.title: My birthday celebrations 2018
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Story of tiny My Birthday Bucket-list - most memorable 📝 in 2k18
Story of this tiny house-stylish small house hotel in the woods!!!! We escape routine to focus on the surrounding, regular hobbies of birthday celebrations 🎉 
This tiny house is unique idea of N&Me
Its is secret forest locations outside of @NH
Really happy to share a travel related post today... past years i was celebrated my birthdays in different location (TN,Dubai,Bahamas.....) this year we went to a tiny house for overnight trip is awesome 
I stayed in a tiny house for the first time ... cabin in-the woods.It was magnificent ,cozy , comfort that is as simple as stylish.For my bdy my hubby was browsing for some places and he got some suggestions of tiny house with beautiful pictures. He thought it would be a fun idea to celebrate my bdy there ... Gateway house is a company that rents out tiny cabins in the woods outside of city (recently opened)It would be 2-3 hrs drive from major cities 
They don’t tell u the exact address until you book ur stay.It should be a privacy of atmosphere 
We booked a night near Boston location few days before , they sent us location exactly with playlist of the drive. We had a beautiful drive and soon pulled-up to gateway sign. I was sort to freaking out excitement and anxious about turning of mobile phone off. Ww drove down a dirt path with full of snow ❄️ with many cabins around 25.
The place was packed with guest but totally quiet
One  cabin is far from another one but we could see there was other life around liked it ..peace &quiet but not complete isolated. From my place we can see 3 cabins . Each cabin has a name out cabin was named #rose 
Cabin has gorgeous glass window out of the forest and with mini kitchen... I cooked Indian food tonight and morning (Dosa/Idly). Inside the cabin one tiny electric toilet /library is there 
I kept my phone in a box until the day has completed (goal- notification free )They will provide campfire kit due to very cold weather we couldn’t stay outside.We did simple balloon decoration and we ordered one cake 🎂 along d drive.... and i cut d cake at 12 ⏰ &took some pictures of the d cabin indoor and from outside. @getawayhouse

🚊🚂🚉🚞Train travel is usually more comfortable and safer for pregnant women because of smoother rides, better facilities, and easier movement.🤰

Comfort & space 
Train : More legroom, wider seats, can walk freely through carriages
Bus& car: Less legroom, narrower seats, limited ability to move around during the journey

Ability to Move
Train: Easier to get up and walk along the aisles
Bus &car:Usually cramped-walking possible only during stops

Ride Smoothness
Train :Smoother ride, less bumpiness in most cases
Bus& car:Often bumpier, especially on uneven roads, which can cause discomfort or nausea

Access to Restrooms
Bus:Generally better and cleaner restrooms onboard
Car& bus :Limited restroom facilities, sometimes unavailable or less hygienic

Duration & Stops
Train:Usually faster and more reliable schedules, predictable stops
Bus &car:Potential delays due to traffic, more stops, longer travel time

Risk of Motion Sickness
Train:Lower risk due to smoother ride
Bus&car:Higher risk, especially on winding or rough roads

Safety
Train:Generally safe; less risk of sudden braking or accidents
Bus&car:More prone to sudden stops or accidents due to road conditions

Convenience
Train:Usually runs on fixed schedules with stations
Train&car:More flexible routes, but can be less predictable with delays

Noise & Crowds
Train:Usually less crowded and noisy compared to buses
Bus:Can be crowded, noisy, and less comfortable during peak times

Anyone is traveling more frequent  during pregnancy  plz take care of everything 
Happy journey : )
